16/03/2008
SKOPJE, Macedonia -- The primary political parties agreed on Saturday (March 15th) to maintain a minority government until the NATO summit in April, after the Democratic Party of Albanians (DPA) decided to leave the ruling coalition, the Foreign Ministry said.
"The government of Macedonia will continue to function as a minority government until the [NATO] summit in Bucharest," Foreign Minister Antonio Milososki told journalists after a government session, convened by President Branko Crvenkovski.
Macedonia has been an official candidate to join the EU since December 2005 and hopes to receive an invitation to join NATO at the Alliance's next summit on April 2nd.
(AFP, Makfax, A1, Makfax - 15/03/08)
